{"version":"1.2","person":{"datePublished":"2023-11-23","name":"Henry de Tregoz First Baron de Tregoz","nameForms":[{"lang":"en","fullText":"Henry de Tregoz First Baron de Tregoz","parts":[{"type":"http://gedcomx.org/Given","value":"Henry"},{"type":"http://gedcomx.org/Surname","value":"de Tregoz"},{"type":"http://gedcomx.org/Suffix","value":"First Baron de Tregoz"}],"order":"EUROTYPIC"}],"alternateName":"Henry of Wigginholt","gender":"Male","lifespan":"1250–1316","fullLifespan":"before 1250–about 1316","memoryArtifacts":[{"memoryType":"STORY","url":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/dascloud/patron/v2/TH-7701-127189-1367-53/dist.txt?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","memoryUrl":"https://www.familysearch.org/photos/artifacts/179223386","headline":"He was a baron, and later, his son followed in his footsteps ","description":"(Check son's profile)","@type":"MediaObject"}],"popularStory":{"memoryType":"STORY","url":"https://sg30p0.familysearch.org/service/records/storage/dascloud/patron/v2/TH-7701-127189-1367-53/dist.txt?ctx=ArtCtxPublic","memoryUrl":"https://www.familysearch.org/photos/artifacts/179223386","headline":"He was a baron, and later, his son followed in his footsteps ","description":"(Check son's profile)","@type":"MediaObject"},"birthPlace":{"address":"East Preston, Sussex, England","geo":{"latitude":50.80903,"longitude":-0.47894,"@type":"GeoCoordinates"},"@type":"Place"},"deathDate":"+1316","deathPlace":{"address":"Wigginholt, Thakeham, Sussex, England","@type":"Place"},"userCertifiedLifeSummary":"Biography\n\"HENRY DE TREGOZ, probably son and heir of Henry de Tregoz, was summoned to attend the King and for service in Gascony, June 1294, for foreign service, May 1297, and to a military council at Rochester, August following. In November 1295 he was granted protection as he was going to Scotland with Earl de Warenne. He was repeatedly summoned against the Scots from 1297 to 1323, was ordered to remain on the Scottish border during the winter of 1315, and was also a Commissioner, 1300 and 1311, to recruit men from Surrey and Sussex for service in Scotland. In March 1296/7 he was ordered to aid the sheriffs of Surrey and Sussex in punishing the disturbers of the realm, being also a Commissioner concerning the clergy, for many of whom he vouched. He was a Justice of oyer and terminer in Sussex, 1299 and 1300, and of oyer and terminer and jail delivery in Sussex, Surrey and Kent, 1314; a Commissioner for the suppression of vagabonds in Sussex, 1303; and in 1321 he was appointed to aid in the enforcement of peace in the realm. He was Knight of the Shire for Sussex in the Parliament which met at Lincoln in 1301; and his seal, as Dominus de Garynges, was attached to the letter of the Barons to the Pope, February 1300/1. He was summoned to Parliament from 12 November 1304 to 14 March 1321/22, by writs directed Henrico Tregoz, whereby he is held to have become LORD TREGOZ. He was granted letters of protection to go on pilgrimage to the shrine of St. Edmund of Pontigny, 21 June 1305, and he, together with his wife, was summoned to the Coronation of Edward II in 1308. He died probably shortly after 2 June 1323\".\n\nOn which date he was discharged from a muster against the Scots because of the truce. There is no further mention of his name. Thomas, who was probably son of Henry, appears as lord of Goring in 1316. but the issue of writs until 1323 suggests that Thomas's tenure of Goring is not evidence of Henry's death, although Salzman considers that it is and that the Henry sum. up to 1323 was his younger brother.\n\nMore Information\n\"Sir Henry Tregoze had succeeded his parents and ancestors in their Sussex estates, before he became head of his family; and about 1271 he sold his manor at Denne or Warnham, co. Sussex to Rosa de Oyly of Raunton, in Staffordshire. In 3rd Edw. I. it was found that Henry Tregoze claimed wrecks in Palynge hundred, and assize of bread and ale in the vill of Goring; and, moreover, that he had appropriated to himself free warren there.\n\n\"This Sir Henry Tregoze married Margaret, daughter and heiress of his neighbour, John de Goring, of co. Sussex; through which match some represent the family as acquiring Goring lordship; but it has been shown that the Tregozes held property there nearly a century before. Sir Henry was, however, also lord of Wykenholle, co. Sussex; and in importance almost exceeded his great deceased kinsman John Baron Tregoze; for during the reigns of Edward I, and Edward II. 1294 and 1322, Sir Henry Tregoze, having acquired much renown in the Scotch wars, was summoned to Parliament as a Baron.\n\n\"In 1296, 24tb Edw. I. he was enrolled, pursuant to an ordinance for the defence of the sea-coast of Sussex, as a knight holding lands within the rape of Arundel, but not resident in the county; and, in 1297, he was among those returned from Sussex and Surrey, as holding lands or rents of 20?. yearly, and as such summoned to perform military service in parts beyond the seas. In 29 Edw. I. he obtained licence from the King to hold a market and fair at Goring; in 1301 we find him styled \" Dominus de Garynnges; \" and in 33rd Edw. I, he had a grant or free warren in Wykenholt, co. Sussex.\n\n\"In 1307 be was a Conservator of Peace in Surrey, and in the following year (1308) in Sussex; in which last year also he was summoned to attend King Edward II's Coronation. In 1309 and in 1313, \" Henry Tregoze \" (sed qu. he or his younger son?) was summoned to Parliament as Knight of the Shire for Sussex as well as by special writ. By the said Margaret de Goring he had issue.\"","events":[{"name":"Birth","sources":"0","year":"1250","date":"before 1250","place":"East Preston, Sussex, England"},{"name":"Marriage","sources":"0","year":"1275","date":"1275","place":"England","type":"Spousal","age":"26","id":"G6W1-1Y4"},{"name":"Birth of Child","sources":"0","year":"1276","date":"about 1276","place":"Goring by Sea, Sussex, England","age":"27","id":"G8W3-TXS"},{"name":"Birth of Child","sources":"0","year":"1278","date":"Abt 1278","place":"Sussex, England","age":"29","id":"G277-TR5"},{"name":"Death of Parent","sources":"0","year":"1293","date":"Bef 1293","place":"East Preston, Sussex, England","age":"42","id":"LT89-V6K"},{"name":"Death","sources":"0","year":"1316","date":"about 1316","place":"Wigginholt, Thakeham, Sussex, England","age":"67"}],"parent":[{"name":"Henry de Tregoz","gender":"Male","lifespan":"1226–1293","birthDate":"A+1226","deathDate":"/+1293","age":66,"@type":"Person","identifier":"LT89-V6K","url":"https://ancestors.familysearch.org/en/LT89-V6K/henry-de-tregoz-1226-1293","published":true}],"sibling":[{"name":"Henry de Tregoz First Baron de Tregoz","gender":"Male","lifespan":"1250–1316","birthDate":"/+1250","deathDate":"A+1316","age":67,"@type":"Person","identifier":"G8W3-Y1V","url":"https://ancestors.familysearch.org/en/G8W3-Y1V/henry-de-tregoz-first-baron-de-tregoz-1250-1316","published":true},{"name":"Isabella de Tregoz","gender":"Female","lifespan":"1275–Female","birthDate":"A+1275","@type":"Person","identifier":"GQSM-MRY","url":"https://ancestors.familysearch.org/en/GQSM-MRY/isabella-de-tregoz-1275","published":true}],"spouse":[{"name":"Margaret de Goring","gender":"Female","lifespan":"1254–Female","birthDate":"A+1254","marriage":{"year":"1275","date":"1275","place":"England"},"@type":"Person","identifier":"G6W1-1Y4","url":"https://ancestors.familysearch.org/en/G6W1-1Y4/margaret-de-goring-1254","published":true}],"children":[{"name":"Thomas de Tregoz 2nd Lord Goring","gender":"Male","lifespan":"1276–1335","birthDate":"A+1276","deathDate":"+1335-05-05","age":59,"otherParentId":"G6W1-1Y4","@type":"Person","identifier":"G8W3-TXS","url":"https://ancestors.familysearch.org/en/G8W3-TXS/thomas-de-tregoz-2nd-lord-goring-1276-1335","published":true},{"name":"Henry de Tregoz","gender":"Male","lifespan":"1278–1323","birthDate":"A+1278","deathDate":"+1323-06-02/","age":45,"otherParentId":"G6W1-1Y4","@type":"Person"